ctol Product Description\nDrug Uses\nStromectol is a semisynthetic anti-parasitic agent providing an anthelmintic effect. Stromectol pills suppress parasites’ functions, causing paralysis of specific types of parasites and destroying them.\nStromectol tablets are prescribed to patients for treatment of infectious diseases such as onchocerciasis (river blindness) and strongyloidiasis. In rare cases, Stromectol is indicated for combination treatment of crusted (Norwegian) scabies or for monotherapy of sarcoptic scabies.\nStromectol provides a broad spectrum anti-parasitic action, and destroys parasites at all life phases, however acting not against all types of parasites. An anti-parasitic effect of Stromectol is not proved against adult microscopic worms Onchocerca volvulus.\nIn order to get rid of pests, an adult patient should take at once one to five tablets of Stromectol 3mg. An alternative and more accurate dosing regimen provides for administration of 150 or 200 mcg of Stromectol per kilogram of body weight at a time.\n\nMissed dose\nIf you were indicated with retreatment of strongyloidiasis or onchocerciasis, and you forgot to take another dose of Stromectol, take it as soon as you remember. Do not take a double dose of the anthelmintic agent, if it is time for the next assigned dosage of Stromectol.\n\nMore Information\nIf necessary, repeated doses of Stromectol can be indicated in one year after the first dose, or, rarer, every three months. After intake of Stromectol, the monitor is required to be sure of eradication of parasites.\n\nStorage\nAnthelmintic agent Stromectol should not be stored above room temperature to 30°C.\n\nStromectol Safety Information\nWarnings\nIf application of Stromectol pills caused intolerance or serious side effects, retreatment with the anti-parasitic agent is not to be indicated. The drug is contraindicated in pregnancy. If you are breastfeeding, take into consideration the anthelmintic agent half-life of up to 20 hours.\n\nDisclaimer\nAll information about parasitic diseases, contained in the review of Stromectol, is intended for reference purposes only. This information is not intended to be used for a substitute for professional medical care of the parasitologist or other healthcare provider. The online pharmacy shall not take responsibility for any damages, caused by improper use of information about anti-parasitic agents, provided in this Stromectol review.\n\nStromectol Side Effects\nStromectol is generally well tolerated. Most unwanted effects are mild to moderate in severity. The patients taking the anti-parasitic agent usually complain of skin reactions (including dry skin, burning sensation, skin irritation or pruritus), diarrhea, nausea, or dizziness. In rare cases, the following unwanted effects of Stromectol can be observed: somnolence, asthenia, fatigue, constipation, anorexia, hives, abdominal pain or cough.\nBlood Pressure\nLasix\n$0.29\nPER PILL\nADD TO CART\nBESTSELLERS\nErectile Dysfunction\nSuper ED Trial Pack\n$3.21\nPER PILL\nADD TO CART\nTODAY’S SALE\nErectile Dysfunction\nBrand Levitra\n$3.70\nPER PILL\nADD TO CART\nErectile Dysfunction\nED Trial Pack\n$4.58\nPER PILL\nADD TO CART\nErectile Dysfunction\nCialis Oral Jelly (Orange)\n$3.15\nPER PILL\nADD TO CART\nSleep Aid\nProvigil\n$0.82\nPER PILL\nADD TO CART\nFree Regmail\nAll Orders From $200\n*Limited Time Offer\nFree\nRegmail\nAll Orders From $200\n*Limited Time Offer\n1m+ Customers\nQuality, Privacy, Secure.\nVery Low Prices\nBest price in the world!\nFast Delivery\n100% Guarantee. Free Airmail shipping.\ntestimonials\ncontact us\nhome\nbestsellers\nCopyright © 2022 Canadian Pharmacy Ltd\nAll rights reserved.\nTestimonials\nContact Us\nHome\nBestsellers\nAntibiotics\nErectile Dysfunction\nMen`s Health\nWeight Loss\nUS: +1 (888) 243-74-06\nUS: +44 (800) 041-87-44\n24 / 7\nCustomer Support",
